sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS visible_contests_count
FROM contests
WHERE is_visible = 1;

SELECT COUNT(participant_id) AS total_participants
FROM contest_history
WHERE contest_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- The cumulative score refers to the total score achieved by each participant across all contests, calculated in the order the contests were started; 
- Participant IDs and usernames are unique for each participant; 
- The contest scores are assumed to be the scores achieved by the participants in each contest.

sql:
SELECT AVG(problems_solved) AS average_problems_solved
FROM contest_history
WHERE contest_id = 0;
